                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1376 a.  </p>
                        <p>Untitled collection of mystical lyrics or ghazalīyāt, in alphabetic order, usually short in length, by the poet Muttaqī.  </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end.  </p>
                        <p>Gilt rulings and sarlawḥ on the opening page (f. 1v), resembling the lower edge from a floriated border, appear to have been extracted from an older illuminated calligraphic leaf.  </p>
                     </note>
